  "texts": [
    "We next evaluated whether ChatGPT could classify the relevance of individual articles.",
    "Within individual specialties, the relation between ChatGPT scores and human scores was much more modest at the article level than at the journal level (Supplemental Figure 1).",
    "Coefficients of determination (R 2) for linear regression ranged from 0.26 (general surgery) to 0.58 (obstetrics and gynecology).",
    "Likewise, global analysis of relevance scores assigned across all specialties revealed a clear but much weaker relation between human and ChatGPT-assigned relevance scores based on the standard error of the regression (Supplemental Figure 2).",
    "The standard error of the regression at the article level was 22.3, which is 2.5-fold greater than the journal-level analysis."
  ],
